race.comment: INVINCIBLE THIEF (5) disappointed last time out but was in better touch earlier in the campaign. The inside draw should see her close to the speed and the claim of Nottle means she'll carry no weight. 13 starts without a win, but she finds a very suitable race today. WHO'S TALKING (6) is another who disappointed here 10 days ago, coming through the same race as INVINCIBLE THIEF. He was slowly away there last start and can bounce back to form with a better jump this time. Rates a leading chance. REGAL BOY (4) ran home strongly over 1200m here last time out and will benefit greatly form the first-up performance. Out to this trip for the first time, but it looks to suit judging by the way he finished off last start and he can make his presence felt. ROCKING IN BROOME (10) has claims on debut. GILES (1) is next best.
